But fingerprints don't lie.
Using magnifying glass, ink, blade, and lantern, Elizar compared the body's fingerprints to those on the pictures.
His eyes didn't fail: it was Alfonso Cano.
That same night, the representative of Puerto Tehad was asked to confirm to the Minister of Defence, Juan Carlos Pinson, that it was the leader of the FARC.
Searching for Fingerprints
The confession received from President Juan Manuel Santos Elizard González at a press conference on the operation against Cano is particularly significant for Sijin of Cali.
A lot of people don't know our job.
Dactiloscopy is a rigorous science, without error, it can play a key role in solving crimes.
