Gazprom, a Russian giant gas manufacturer, wanted to celebrate this pompous event.
More than 500 guests, including four heads of State and Government, took part last Tuesday on the banks of the Baltics, between the orchestra's performance and exquisite snacks, in the opening of the Northern Flow, a new gas pipeline that directly connects Russia and Germany underwater.
